# Report Room — Full Project Audit & Fix Plan

After thoroughly analyzing every file in both the server and client codebases, I've identified **17 issues** ranging from bugs and security holes to dead code and reliability problems. Here's the complete plan.

---

## User Review Required

> [!CAUTION]
> **Security: Plaintext credentials in `connections.json`** — Database passwords are stored in plaintext in a JSON file that could accidentally be committed to git. The `.gitignore` does NOT exclude `connections.json`. This is flagged but considered out of scope for this fix pass (would require an encryption layer).

> [!WARNING]
> **SQL Script Drift** — `01_create_tables.sql` still has a legacy `role` column on the `users` table (`role VARCHAR2(20) DEFAULT 'user' CHECK (role IN ('admin', 'user'))`). The application no longer uses this column since the role-based system was migrated to junction tables. The script also already includes `connection_key` inline, but `05_add_connection_key.sql` duplicates the same ALTER TABLE, which will fail on a fresh install. Both scripts need cleanup.

